    "However, unlike AFT where W is a pairwise matrix, our model treats W as a channel-wise vector that is modified by relative position.",
    "In our model, this recurrent behavior is defined by the time-dependent update of the W KV vectors, formalized in the following equation:",
    "To circumvent any potential degradation of W, we introduce a vector U that separately attends to the current token.",
    "More information about this can be found in Appendix I.",
    "Output gating is implemented in both time-mixing and channel-mixing blocks using the sigmoid of the receptance, σ(r)."
  ]
